<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Simple - but it would require a complete overhaul</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Azeraab">Azeraab</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 8:50 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Simple - but it would require a complete overhaul<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=773" TARGET=_self>Geiger says this subject is worth discussing, so input your ideas on how to fix it.</A> (Min)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>From what I can tell lvl 1 - 5 monsters do up to about 12 damage, 6-15 do about 25, 16-25 do about 50, 26-35 do about 100 and so on. That is in addition to the extra powers (like double attack) that they gain along the way.

<P>So a Hill Giant (lvl in the 30's I believe) will do about 225 damage in the first "round" of attacks (1 bash plus 2 normal attacks). This will instantly kill any character who isnt over 10th lvl, and unless you can feign death or something you will die before you can escape unless you are over 20th lvl.
<P>Attack ability, defense, damage, spell resistance, all seem to be on a similar geometric pattern making it so that a monster 10 levels higher than you is 50 times as powerful as you are.
<P>If these advancement curves were to go along a more linear pattern so with our damage example instead of doubling damage every 10 lvls perhaps increasing it by 10. This would make it so that groups of players could actually kill something significantly higher lvl than they are. This would not only make the game more fun and balanced, but it would promote grouping where the current system actually dissuades groups to some extent.
<P>&gt; Of course we can't really make good suggestion if we don't know
<BR>&gt; how everything is calculated, but at least give them some ideas.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
